Former Nairobi speaker Alex Magelo has urged city residents to support Governor Mike Sonko for him to deliver on promises he made. Magelo said meaningful development can only be realised if the residents throw their weight behind the governor. “The governor needs the support of everyone, regardless of whether they voted for him or not. That is the only way to bring change in Nairobi,” Magelo said. Read: Sonko claims rivals behind Nairobi CBD muggings Speaking to the Star on Wednesday, Magelo asked Sonko to focus on service delivery to residents. He urged the governor to quickly address insecurity, garbage menace and congestion caused by hawkers. "He needs to work hand-in-hand with the police to address the muggings in the city centre," Magelo said. Click here for the latest political news 